This was a lone wolf game - a single wolf vs 11 other people... with a bit of help from 2 people who didn't know who they were!

They were somewhat helped by two things: items and village misinformation. They had 2 clarity potions to give them some info about people's roles.- they managed to hit a power role and a villager with tose
They also had 1 block, 1 night of block immune via potion, 1 extra kill via crossbow and 1 extra shift
Village misinformation - there were 2 people who were incriminated, 1 lycan and 1 wolfpelt - plus 2 BMC showing as wolf
However to counter this the village had 3 intel roles and 3 intel runes - which is very intel heavy for a 12 player game
So to counter THIS the village power roles were all hampered by auras in some way - drunk or concussed.

To solve this the village had 4 ways to get rid of these auras - including incriminated - via 3 potions which that villager had to give away as they were clumsy and unable to use them directly, plus an ethereal armour
So the village would get more powerful as the game went on, countered by the fact that roles would be dying
The BMC had 3 potions to protect themselves - which ended up on the wolf almost immediately when Smugvid (GrandmaGeorgina) was murdered by her own wolf

The disruption orb which caused so many problems was also there as protection for the village (along with the concussed protector who effectively protected 3 people at a time once the wolf knew of their existence). The orb could block a kill to begin with but the wolf had one night of block immunity to get round this
however once they kill someone for the orb, they then have the orb so would always miss a night
